                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">bards kinda took over this ability, and recently they gave us scryers (which is 50 a tick for a lil bit, but not really extendable all that much) level 52 btw...
<br />

<br />
lagarns steals a token amount of mana (no recourse..ie we dont get any of the stolen mana)
<br />

<br />
and our 50ish PBAE stun steals mana from AE (no recourse)
<br />

<br />
mana drain is low level high resist research spell
<br />

<br />
wandering mind is a tap with a small recourse
<br />

<br />
torment of scio has a mana tap (no recourse)
<br />

<br />
<span style="color: orange">What Id like to see in a manadrain/combo</span>
<br />

<br />
60+ spell
<br />
Single Target
<br />
low resist (maybe even make it a curse)
<br />
4-5 min refresh (maybe 8-10 or make it an AA and say 20 mins)
<br />
3-5 tick duration (augmentable with items)
<br />
drain 200 mana a tick with recourse (you get back say half of that)
<br />
medium to low casting cost
<br />
fast cast
<br />
and a stun combination (to prevent spellcasting) (0.0 stun per tick)
<br />

<br />
thoughts? maybe thats the wrong way to go with manadrains...but who knows!
<br />

<br />
serverwide.enchanter : enchanter</span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br /><a href="http://dictionary.reference.com/search?r=67&q=Sell%20Out" target="_blank" class="postlink"><img src="http://www.therunes.net/forums/files/nanyea.gif" border="0" /></a>
