                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><hr /></td>
                        </tr>
                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody"></span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">Scryer's Trespass gives you 500 mana and is basically unresistable (-500 check). 
<br />
You seem to be asking for essentially the same thing, except with more drain on the mob and faster acting.</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
Looking at Trespass, you get 50 mana per tick for 1 minute (10 ticks). That equals 500 mana. However, the recast time is 3 minutes and 20 seconds, which is 33 and 1/3 ticks (we'll just call it 33 ticks to keep it simple). This equals a net regen of about 15 mana per tick, assuming you can cast it everytime it pops up.
<br />

<br />
Theft of Thought gives only 400 mana (assuming it's not resisted). However, the recast time is only 2 minutes (20 ticks). This comes out to 20 mana per tick, again assuming you can find a target every 2 minutes.
<br />

<br />
The difference (and the reason I think Trespass is a better spell) is that as long as trespass isn't resisted, you get the full 500 mana from it. Theft of Though, even with a -1000 resist check is partially resisted, especially against higher level mobs, and you only get a fraction of the mana.
<br />

<br />
Our mana over time taps are fine as they are. But I think a 60+ straight tap is something we should get. Perhaps same recast ToT, but you get a straight 600 mana off it. Also, make it harder to partially resist, or Trespass will still be the superior spell.
<br />

<br />
So, they are completely different spells, and useful in different situations. In PoP, if I need the extra regen, I use Trespass, but with old world stuff, I usually use ToT instead.</span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br /><center>Sage Fadarm
<br />
65th Coercer of Pillars of Honor
<br />
Mithaniel Marr Server</center></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
