                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Actually, mana pool doesn't affect how much mana is returned by ToT. This is easy to test. My brother plays a bard, one time he was out of mana and I told him to duel me so I could try something out. He did, and I tapped him...for a full return on mana back to me. Also, I tested this when I used to 2 box. I made a level 1 character (with a mana pool of like 50) ran him oom dueled him and ToT'd...again full return. The amount returned isn't based on the amount of mana your target has. I don't know what it's based off of, but I'll leave you with this. In LDoN, in a level 65 adventure, when I use ToT, it usually returns 2-3% of my mana. In a level 60 adventure, when I use ToT, it usually returns around 9% of my mana. There are some mobs in a 60 adventure, however, that return less, closer to the 2-3% mark than the 9% mark. But, I never get more than about 3% mana return in a 65 dungeon with ToT. I have about a 4100 mana pool (yeah, it sucks) with Tranquility.</span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br /><center>Sage Fadarm
<br />
65th Coercer of Pillars of Honor
<br />
Mithaniel Marr Server</center></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
