                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">As far as ToT and testing it against PCs, that has been around for a long time and I was actually warned by a Guide and was told it was a bug, although this was back when Najib was a long time ago, like when I was 54 or so.  I had figured out the same thing Fadarm mentioned and pulls in Karnor's could get pretty hairy.  I usually had it worked out ahead of time to /duel a party member if I was low on mana.  Yes, that's right, we dueled during a bad pull.  All of the times I did this was with Rangers, Shadow Knights or Paladins.  I would ToT them for their mana.  When I figured it out was when a SK said to me, "I had no mana so I don't know why you were doing that" so that's when it dawned on me.  Now I was told it was a bug with PCs and I got warned for taking advantage of it.
<br />

<br />
As far as new spells are concerned.  I always thought they should upgrade Mana Sieve, I mean its level 34 and in some fights in PoP the enchanter core was asked to use it.  Even if they added a new one in that was say an upgrade, I'm not sure if I was would use it on a regular basis.  I have a pretty good sized mana pool but I only have 2 FT items and they are both for 1), I do have MC3.  In outdoor zones, I fight on a leezard and I have never had a mana problem.  In LDoN, the only time I have mana issues is if I have to cast VoQ while in the dungeon.</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
