                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">About ToT being bugged on PCs and not to be abused.....I personally dont think it's limited to PC. I think every type of "tap" spells in the game do that. Have a 65 SK do his best lifetap on a lv 1 mob with like 20 hp. He'll get full recourse, so I assume its the same about mana. Another example....cast scryer's on a mob just before he dies. You'll get full recourse even if he dies after 1st tick. 
<br />
So i dont think the "tap" lines of spell actually takes into account the hp/mana a mob has, it just gives you the amount your spell can get.
<br />

<br />
About ToT giving next to nothing on high level mobs, I thought ToT was simply broken on 55+ mobs and only gave like 0-2% mana back.../shrug</span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=413525" target="_blank" class="postlink"><span style="font-weight: bold"><span style="text-decoration: underline">Fliry</span></span></a>
